title: Wolves defeat Warriors on volleyball court
text:
Wolves defeat Warriors on volleyball court Oct 09, 2015 
BY ANDY KRUTSINGER 
Mt. Pleasant News 
WINFIELD â€” The Winfield-Mt. Union and WACO volleyball teams faced off in a North Division showdown on Thursday night in Winfield. The Wolves won the first two sets, 25-19 and 25-13, before falling to the Warriors, 25-11, in the third, but W-MU closed things out, 25-14 in the fourth set for a 3-1 victory. 
Lexee Hartsock and Pearl Krieger-Coble led the Wolves with nine kills apiece in the win. Cassidy Lennie had four kills, Lauren Jamison had two, and the trio of Hannah Buffington, Sophie Kongable and Caitlin Jamison had three kills apiece. 
C. Jamison also led in assists for the Wolves, with 15 and scooped up 14 digs in the win. L. Jamison was the leading digger, with 19. Kongable had 13 digs, Kenzie Scott and Kara Wade each had eight, Lennie had five, Krieger-Coble had three and Hartsock had two. 
The Wolves, who have won five of their last six games, moved to 17-14 with the win and 6-2 in conference play. They will travel to Wapello on Tuesday, Oct. 13. W-MU defeated the Arrows, 2-1 in the SEISC tournament consolation bracket. 
WACO fell to 6-16 with the loss, and 1-7 in conference. The Warriors go to Davis County for a tournament tomorrow (Saturday).
